```

If you look at the else block here, the builder object has not even been instantiated. You are trying to call instance methods on the object. NotificationManager.notify is called twice if the code in the else block executes.

My two cents:

1. Do not update textviews directly from the service, it is not safe. Send them to the activity through an intent if you want.

2. Sending notifications is possible through a Service, but should still be avoided if possible. If you want to do it anyway, please refactor the code, and use a PendingIntent to associate an activity to handle the notification.

**Sample Code**

Adding sample code which requires a separate Activity called NotificationView to handle click event on the notification. You can remove the PendingIntent related code if you do not want this dependency. I have also not included any other parts of your code for brevity.

Note that I create the notification channel in the onCreate (only once).

